'''''Clarkella''''' is a [[Monotypic taxon|monotypic]] [[genus]] of [[flowering plant]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Rubiaceae]].<ref name="Hooker1880">[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/455642#page/50/mode/1up Hooker, Joseph Dalton. 1880. Flora of British India 3(7): 46.]</ref> The genus contains only one [[species]], viz. '''''Clarkella nana''''', which is native to [[India]], [[China]], [[Uttarakhand]], the Western [[Himalayas]], [[Burma]] and [[Thailand]].<ref name="WCSP">[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=41647 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families, ''Clarkella'']</ref><ref>Craib, William Grant. 1931.  Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information Kew 1931: 216, ''Clarkella siamensis'' from Thailand</ref>

